  PETROVA: C++23 has std::expected with monadic operations, but those aren't ergonomic for early-return. What IRO needs is:

  #define IRO_TRY(expr) \
    ({ \
      auto&& _result = (expr); \
      if (!_result.has_value()) \
        return ::iro::freestanding::unexpected(_result.error()); \
      ::iro::freestanding::move(_result.value()); \
    })

  // Usage:
  auto slice = IRO_TRY(make_boxed_slice<int>(n, gfp_kernel()));

  GNU statement expressions make this work. Clang 18 supports them. It's not standard, but neither is kernel C.

